'''''The New Rebellion''''' is a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] novel by [[Kristine Kathryn Rusch]] and was published in [[1996]] by [[Bantam Spectra]]. The novel takes place in [[17 ABY/Legends|17 ABY]], shortly after the [[Black Fleet Crisis]].

==Publisher's summary==
''Somewhere in the galaxy, millions suddenly perish&mdash;a disruption of the Force so shocking it is felt by Luke at his Jedi academy and by Leia on Coruscant. While Leia must deal with an assassination attempt, a rumored plot against the New Republic, and allegations that Han Solo is involved, Luke seeks out a former Jedi student who may hold the key to the mass destruction. But Brakiss is only the bait in a deadly trap set by a master of the dark side who is determined to rule as emperor. He's targeted Luke, Leia, and Leia's Jedi children to die. Then billions will follow, in a holocaust unequaled in galactic history''.

==Plot summary==
The [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] [[Kueller]] sets in motion a plan to bring down the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] and the new generation of [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]]. First, he [[Death/Legends|kills]] over a million innocent natives of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Pydyr]] and then sets off a [[Bomb/Legends|bomb]] in the New Republic Senate Hall.

As [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] searches for the one behind all of this, [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]] has her own problems arising from conflicts with newly elected former [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperials]] in the senate, and the framing of her husband [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] by the [[Smuggler/Legends|smuggler]] [[Jarril]], who is suspected to be responsible for the senate bombing.

As Han Solo travels with [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] to the [[Smuggler's Run/Legends|Smuggler's Run]] to investigate the actions of Jarril in hopes of getting to the bottom of the Senate bombing, Luke Skywalker visits [[Brakiss]] on [[Telti/Legends|Telti]] looking for information, and [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] heads to The Run after Han Solo who he fears is in danger.

Meanwhile, [[Cole Fardreamer]], with the aid of [[R2-D2/Legends|R2-D2]] and [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]], discovers a plot to install all New Republic [[X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-wings]] with remote detonators. Leia becomes aware of this and concedes her position as [[President/Legends|president]] to [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]] in order to rescue Luke from [[Kueller]] who has taken him [[Prisoner/Legends|prisoner]] on [[Almania/Legends|Almania]]. After Han rescues Lando, rather than Lando rescuing Han, from the clutches of the [[Crime lord/Legends|crime lord]] [[Nandreeson]], and the two of them aide hundreds of smugglers after an accidental bombing of the Run, Han also heads to [[Almania/Legends|Almania]] to rescue Luke.

Han arrives at [[Almania/Legends|Almania]] in the midst of a vicious battle between [[New Republic Defense Force/Legends|New Republic forces]] led by [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] and Kueller's fleet. Han is also met by [[Talon Karrde]] and [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]] who have brought [[Ysalamiri/Legends|ysalamiri]] to assist in the battle against Kueller. After a long grueling battle against Kueller, in which Kueller has gained a tremendous amount of power fueled by Luke's own anger at himself for allowing Kueller to fall to the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]], Luke is preparing himself for death at Kueller's hands as Han arrives on the scene with the ysalamiri, sapping both Luke and Kueller of their power, and in doing so allows Leia to finish Kueller with two lethal [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] shots.

R2-D2 and C-3PO simultaneously thwart Kueller's plan to detonate millions of [[Droid/Legends|droids]] across [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy]]. This enables Leia to return to [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] and regain her post as president from Mon Mothma.

==Continuity==
''[[The Black Fleet Crisis]]'' ([[1996]]-[[1997|97]]), threatening [[Han Solo/Legends|Han]] only reinforced [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia's]] dedication to the office of [[Chief of State (New Republic)/Legends|Chief of State]], and she refused to back down in the face of allegations that she was too personally invested in the threat to the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]]. Here, she surrendered her office when [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke]] was threatened. The inconsistency was the result of two stories in near-concurrent development, but hindsight suggested that perhaps Leia was indeed worn down by the time she faced the [[Almanian Uprising|Almanian crisis]]. She did, after all, temporarily step down from office in [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]].<ref name="ERC" />

